* :QhexXoP3ZxHB6DZS: A window can be split horizontally with C-x 2, or vertically with C-x 3. That can be repeated. To make the current window occupy the entire screen, use C-x 1. To move the cursor from one window to another (in the same frame), use `C-x o`, or in move-submode, simply `o`.
